			<div class="content" id="post-content-2232285">
									

<p>Scince it's written up this way, I'm forced to react to this as a tale-form SCP. The result?</p>
<p>Beyond the flowery, purple prose, this is a simple Thing What Kills You, which makes you speak in bad poetry if ypu spend too much time near it. The format screw makes it near-worthless as any sort of scientific document- what's the audible range of the SCP, for instance?</p>
<p>Knowing that it's a crossover with Sweeny Todd doesn't improve the article in my mind, since it wholly relies on the rhyming to be good.</p>

